modules.description: Provides functions to establish and manage network connections using raw sockets, including sending and receiving packets at the link layer. Operates on file descriptors and raw byte buffers for low-level network communication. Used to implement custom network protocols or interface with hardware devices directly.

Provides functions to write and read network packets using raw sockets, including writing single or multiple buffers as a single packet, and listening for incoming traffic. Operates on buffer types like Cstruct.t and Io_page.t, and interacts with MAC addresses and file descriptors. Used to establish a connection to a network interface, manage packet transmission, and monitor device statistics.
